On June 10, 2009, Vice President Biden hosted two conference calls with governors and mayors/county executives from across the country to discuss the implementation of the Recovery Act. The conference calls included elected officials such as Governor John Baldacci (D-ME), Governor Dave Heineman (R-NE), Governor Bill Ritter (D-CO), Mayor Norm Archibald (R – Abilene, TX), Mayor William V. 'Bill' Bell (D – Durham, NC), Mayor Dean DePiero (D – Parma, OH), Mayor Molly Ward (D – Hampton, VA), County Commissioner Harry B. Montoya (D – Santa Fe County, NM), and County Executive Pat McCarthy (D – Pierce County, WA). The purpose of the calls was to discuss the progress and implementation of the Recovery Act.